not me.

262
00:15:12,028 --> 00:15:15,596
- I'll leave you two
alone to discuss.
- I'll come with you.

263
00:15:15,698 --> 00:15:17,465
- I have a couple of questions.
- Alex.

264
00:15:17,566 --> 00:15:20,051
Think about what you
want to do for a second, OK?

265
00:15:20,153 --> 00:15:21,569
I'll be right back.

266
00:15:32,048 --> 00:15:34,932
You are not having the surgery.

267
00:15:36,853 --> 00:15:39,219
I need you to not
talk medicine to me.

268
00:15:39,321 --> 00:15:41,322
Talk to me like I'm your friend,

269
00:15:41,424 --> 00:15:43,591
like I'm the guy whose
cereal you eat in the morning,

270
00:15:43,693 --> 00:15:45,392
and tell me what to do.

271
00:15:45,494 --> 00:15:46,805
- Karev...
- Please.

272
00:15:46,829 --> 00:15:48,507
Karev, I can't tell
you what to do.

273
00:15:48,531 --> 00:15:51,165
What if it was Meredith?

274
00:15:51,267 --> 00:15:54,068
What would you do
if you had to choose

275
00:15:54,170 --> 00:15:56,370
between spending a few
more months with Meredith

276
00:15:56,472 --> 00:15:58,722
knowing she was gonna die,

277
00:15:58,824 --> 00:16:01,192
watching her hurt,
watching her sick...

278
00:16:02,745 --> 00:16:05,145
or spending the rest of
your life with someone

279
00:16:05,248 --> 00:16:08,199
who looked like Meredith,
but wasn't her anymore.

280
00:16:08,301 --> 00:16:10,668
She's the one good thing
that ever happened to me.

281
00:16:10,770 --> 00:16:13,070
The one good thing.

282
00:16:13,172 --> 00:16:16,240
So I need to know what
to do. I need you to tell me,

283
00:16:16,342 --> 00:16:18,275
what if it was Meredith?

284
00:16:21,163 --> 00:16:23,664
I would ask her to
have the surgery.

285
00:16:27,537 --> 00:16:29,803
You couldn't remember anything.

286
00:16:29,905 --> 00:16:31,672
You didn't know my name.

287
00:16:31,774 --> 00:16:35,359
You didn't know who Derek was,
you didn't know who Alex was.

288
00:16:35,445 --> 00:16:39,096
- You couldn't remember
how to speak.
- Why don't I remember this?

289
00:16:39,198 --> 00:16:41,318
The tumor is sitting right
in the middle of everything

290
00:16:41,350 --> 00:16:43,567
that makes you you.

291
00:16:43,669 --> 00:16:48,256
I was standing there talking
to you exactly like I am now,

292
00:16:48,358 --> 00:16:52,809
only you weren't
there. You weren't you.

293
00:16:52,912 --> 00:16:54,945
You were gone.

294
00:16:56,082 --> 00:16:59,350
- So what do I do?
- Swender has a patient,

295
00:16:59,452 --> 00:17:02,870
female, 22 years old,
metastatic melanoma.

296
00:17:02,972 --> 00:17:05,823
- Alison Clark?
- After three months of IL2,

297
00:17:05,925 --> 00:17:08,208
her mets were gone. All of them.

298
00:17:10,079 --> 00:17:12,379
You're not having this surgery.

299
00:17:15,101 --> 00:17:18,586
Don't do it. That's my vote.

300
00:17:18,688 --> 00:17:21,088
Don't have the
surgery. I didn't.

301
00:17:21,190 --> 00:17:23,274
I freakin' hate surgery.

302
00:17:25,094 --> 00:17:28,229
I'm hallucinating, Alison.

303
00:17:28,331 --> 00:17:30,798
I have really long
conversations with dead people,

304
00:17:30,900 --> 00:17:33,835
and I see things that aren't...

305
00:17:33,937 --> 00:17:37,638
Right now, I'm pretty certain

306
00:17:37,740 --> 00:17:39,724
there aren't birds
flying over your head,

307
00:17:39,825 --> 00:17:42,460
because this is a hospital
and that would be weird,

308
00:17:42,562 --> 00:17:46,313
but that's what I'm seeing.
I have a brain tumor.

309
00:17:46,415 --> 00:17:48,816
Am I really not gonna
let them cut it out?

310
00:17:48,918 --> 00:17:51,586
I didn't let them cut out mine.

311
00:17:51,688 --> 00:17:56,090
It's like, OK, one minute
I'm this college kid,

312
00:17:56,192 --> 00:18:00,160
rowing crew and being an
idiot and forgetting my sunscreen

313
00:18:00,262 --> 00:18:03,247
and thinking it doesn't
matter because I'm me,

314
00:18:03,349 --> 00:18:06,150
and life has worked
out pretty well for me.

315
00:18:06,252 --> 00:18:08,852
And then, the next minute
they're cutting into my body

316
00:18:08,955 --> 00:18:10,687
every other week.

317
00:18:11,857 --> 00:18:14,158
I had 15 surgeries.

318
00:18:14,928 --> 00:18:18,713
And then I said enough.

319
00:18:18,815 --> 00:18:23,417
Forget it. I'll row crew
in heaven, or whatever.

320
00:18:24,554 --> 00:18:29,323
And then the IL2
worked. It worked.

321
00:18:29,425 --> 00:18:34,628
I come here every three
weeks, I get my medicine, and...

322
00:18:34,730 --> 00:18:37,364
I don't have a brain
tumor anymore.

323
00:18:42,188 --> 00:18:45,356
Charlie, if we admit you, if we
do what you're asking us to do,

324
00:18:45,458 --> 00:18:48,659
the pain in your leg,
there's no way of knowing

325
00:18:48,761 --> 00:18:49,989
if amputation will cure it.

326
00:18:50,013 --> 00:18:51,893
- But it might.
- Yes, it might.

327
00:18:51,964 --> 00:18:53,464
And once I get the prosthetic...

328
00:18:53,566 --> 00:18:55,877
It will be months
before I can even begin

329
00:18:55,901 --> 00:18:57,301
fitting you with a prosthetic.

330
00:18:57,403 --> 00:18:59,883
Which won't feel anything
like a new leg, by the way.

331
00:18:59,939 --> 00:19:02,873
It'll feel like five pounds of
metal that hurts and pinches.

332
00:19:02,975 --> 00:19:04,425
And what if the Army says no,

333
00:19:04,527 --> 00:19:06,154
what if they don't
take you back?

334
00:19:06,178 --> 00:19:09,147
- They will. Chances are...
- You want to take that chance?

335
00:19:09,249 --> 00:19:12,233
You're asking me to
remove one of your limbs.

336
00:19:12,335 --> 00:19:14,563
You think I don't know that,
you think I want to cut my leg off?

337
00:19:14,587 --> 00:19:17,521
Of course not. Am I
sure about this? No.

338
00:19:17,623 --> 00:19:20,107
The only thing I'm sure
about is I'm in hell right now.

339
00:19:20,209 --> 00:19:23,027
That I'm sure of.

340
00:19:23,129 --> 00:19:24,428
I've lost everything.

341
00:19:24,513 --> 00:19:26,897
Everything I've worked
for, everything I care about,

342
00:19:26,999 --> 00:19:29,466
and I traded it in for a
six-times-a-day pain pill habit

343
00:19:29,568 --> 00:19:32,570
that doesn't work. So don't waste
both our time trying to scare me,

344
00:19:32,672 --> 00:19:36,006
because you don't scare me.

345
00:19:36,108 --> 00:19:39,509
After everything I've been
through, nothing scares me.

346
00:19:43,232 --> 00:19:45,349
So are we gonna do this or not?

347
00:19:50,039 --> 00:19:54,291
Dr. Robbins, Dr. Bailey just
performed Seattle Grace's

348
00:19:54,393 --> 00:19:56,760
first single-incision
gallbladder removal.

349
00:19:56,862 --> 00:19:59,930
- Oh, wow! Cool!
- Through the patient's
belly button.

350
00:20:00,032 --> 00:20:03,300
- And now it's kind of creepy.
- No, you should've seen it.

351
00:20:03,402 --> 00:20:05,730
No scars, no bleeding,
and about half the time

352
00:20:05,754 --> 00:20:07,866
it would've taken
laparascopically.

353
00:20:07,890 --> 00:20:09,139
You want to do one after lunch?

354
00:20:09,241 --> 00:20:11,209
- I've got another colon.
- You don't mind?

355
00:20:11,311 --> 00:20:15,512
Oh... So I guess I'm on
my own for this afternoon?

356
00:20:15,615 --> 00:20:19,000
My neuroblastoma? No,
don't worry. You don't have to.

357
00:20:19,102 --> 00:20:22,253
You'll have the rest of your
life to do neuroblastomas.

358
00:20:22,355 --> 00:20:25,339
- Then I'll see you after lunch.
- OK.

359
00:20:26,993 --> 00:20:30,461
- Chief?
- Yes, Dr. Robbins?

360
00:20:32,948 --> 00:20:37,017
- Chief...
- Did you want
to tell me something?

361
00:20:37,136 --> 00:20:39,119
I am going to cry.

362
00:20:39,221 --> 00:20:42,406
I just want you to know that
I know it's going to happen,

363
00:20:42,508 --> 00:20:45,109
and I just want
you to ignore it.

364
00:20:45,211 --> 00:20:46,955
And I'm not crying
because I'm upset.

365
00:20:46,979 --> 00:20:48,991
It's just what happens
when I get mad

366
00:20:49,015 --> 00:20:52,599
- at people of authority.
- You're mad at me?

367
00:20:52,702 --> 00:20:53,982
I am mad at you.

368
00:20:54,070 --> 00:20:56,687
And I'm crying because
you're the boss, my boss,

369
00:20:56,789 --> 00:20:58,683
which brings up issues
with authority and my dad,

370
00:20:58,707 --> 00:21:00,241
who you remind me of.

371
00:21:00,343 --> 00:21:02,604
Not that you're old. But
you command respect.

372
00:21:02,628 --> 00:21:04,206
People respect you.
I mean, I know I do.

373
00:21:04,230 --> 00:21:06,830
I know Bailey does.
Which is why I am mad.

374
00:21:06,932 --> 00:21:10,534
Because it's wrong,
sir, it's wrong and mean

375
00:21:10,636 --> 00:21:12,917
to use a robot to lure Bailey
back to general surgery.

376
00:21:12,971 --> 00:21:14,438
I don't have a robot.

377
00:21:14,540 --> 00:21:18,241
All I have are little kids.
They're not as fun as a robot.

378
00:21:18,344 --> 00:21:21,712
And they're not shiny
and new and silver,

379
00:21:21,814 --> 00:21:25,248
and they don't have things coming
out of their belly buttons but...

380
00:21:25,351 --> 00:21:28,469
I will fight you.
And I will win.

381
00:21:28,571 --> 00:21:31,488
- Sir.
- You think you can fight me

382
00:21:31,590 --> 00:21:33,140
and win?

383
00:21:34,376 --> 00:21:39,730
- Yes.
- Good luck.

384
00:21:39,832 --> 00:21:44,952
Because I have something
you don't have. I have joy! Sir.

385
00:21:49,074 --> 00:21:50,994
<i>Dr. Toretto, pathology.</i>

386
00:21:51,043 --> 00:21:54,712
<i>Dr. Toretto, pathology.</i>

387
00:21:54,814 --> 00:21:58,682
- What's going on?
- We're going over Izzie's
IL2 schedule.

388
00:21:58,784 --> 00:22:00,150
Oh, for after the surgery?

389
00:22:06,308 --> 00:22:09,326
I decided not to
have the surgery.

390
00:22:09,428 --> 00:22:13,013
- What?
- Maybe we should come back.

391
00:22:13,115 --> 00:22:14,514
Dr. Yang.

392
00:22:19,088 --> 00:22:20,904
- You're having the surgery.
- What?

393
00:22:21,006 --> 00:22:23,435
- Shepherd said this is
your last shot.
- But I just...

394
00:22:23,459 --> 00:22:26,259
I am your husband, I say
that you are having the surgery!

395
00:22:26,361 --> 00:22:29,279
What happened to,
"This is your decision..."

396
00:22:29,381 --> 00:22:32,032
That was when I thought you
were gonna make the right one!

397
00:22:32,135 --> 00:22:34,801
You chose wrong, so you don't
make this decision on your own,

398
00:22:34,903 --> 00:22:36,186
you married me!

399
00:22:36,288 --> 00:22:39,623
It's not just your life at stake
anymore! It's my life, too!

400
00:22:39,726 --> 00:22:42,493
My life with you!

401
00:22:42,595 --> 00:22:44,578
You can tell Swender
whatever you want,

402
00:22:44,680 --> 00:22:48,916
but I'm telling Shepherd, and
you, you are having the surgery!

403
00:23:05,451 --> 00:23:07,695
She's your friend, but
that doesn't give the right

404
00:23:07,719 --> 00:23:09,597
to talk her out of a surgery
you know nothing about.

405
00:23:09,621 --> 00:23:11,956
You're Swender's resident.

406
00:23:12,058 --> 00:23:14,135
What you did was
inappropriate, it is unprofessional.

407
00:23:14,159 --> 00:23:17,060
- You crossed a line!
- No, she didn't. I did.

408
00:23:17,162 --> 00:23:19,430
I'm the one who convinced
Izzie not to have surgery.

409
00:23:19,532 --> 00:23:21,915
I'm the one you should
be yelling at right now.

410
00:23:26,288 --> 00:23:28,806
Well, I'm gonna go now.

411
00:23:29,909 --> 00:23:33,594
Unless you wanna
apologize... OK.

412
00:23:38,584 --> 00:23:41,852
My mother disappeared
right in front of me.

413
00:23:41,954 --> 00:23:43,920
Everything she had,
everything she was,

414
00:23:44,022 --> 00:23:45,356
her dignity, her memory.

415
00:23:45,458 --> 00:23:47,625
In the end, she
wasn't even my mother.

416
00:23:47,710 --> 00:23:49,209
Izzie is not your mother.

417
00:23:49,311 --> 00:23:51,679
She doesn't have an
untreatable brain condition.

418
00:23:51,781 --> 00:23:54,147
She has a tumor.
And it can be treated.

419
00:23:54,249 --> 00:23:55,782
Don't make this personal.

420
00:23:55,885 --> 00:23:58,535
- I wasn't.
- You went to Izzie,
as her friend,

421
00:23:58,637 --> 00:23:59,881
and you made up
her mind for her.

422
00:23:59,905 --> 00:24:02,590
As my resident, go
back there and change it.

423
00:24:02,692 --> 00:24:05,809
Because this
tumor will kill her.

424
00:24:10,499 --> 00:24:12,599
Quick consult, Dr. Yang?

425
00:24:15,037 --> 00:24:16,737
What are you doing?

426
00:24:19,458 --> 00:24:23,276
The reason I haven't told my mother
I'm back is part of me is still there.

427
00:24:23,378 --> 00:24:25,880
I made a commitment to
the Army I wasn't able to fulfill.

428
00:24:25,982 --> 00:24:28,265
If my unit hadn't been
destroyed, I'd be there.

429
00:24:28,367 --> 00:24:31,551
No wonder I can't
sleep at night,

430
00:24:31,653 --> 00:24:34,638
or look my mother in the eye.
You and I can't move forward.

431
00:24:34,740 --> 00:24:35,973
My work there isn't done.

432
00:24:36,075 --> 00:24:39,826
And until it is, I have
no business being here.

433
00:24:42,431 --> 00:24:45,766
So... I've decided to go back.

434
00:24:47,470 --> 00:24:49,636
I have to go.

435
00:24:49,738 --> 00:24:53,624
- Cristina, come on.
- What am I supposed to say?

436
00:24:53,726 --> 00:24:58,746
- I could use your support.
- You don't have it.

437
00:25:05,871 --> 00:25:10,173
Dr. Torres? Dr. O'Malley?

438
00:25:10,275 --> 00:25:13,027
I just wanted to apologize.

439
00:25:13,129 --> 00:25:14,894
- It's OK.
- You don't have to.

440
00:25:14,997 --> 00:25:19,550
I do. 'Cause you were
trying to do your job in there,

441
00:25:19,652 --> 00:25:22,218
your job is to put people back
together, not take 'em apart.

442
00:25:22,320 --> 00:25:23,687
I get that.

443
00:25:25,207 --> 00:25:27,674
I know it doesn't make sense
to you that I want to go back

444
00:25:27,776 --> 00:25:30,344
to a place where
people get hurt and die,

445
00:25:30,446 --> 00:25:34,281
but we're there because
we're trying to help people.

446
00:25:34,383 --> 00:25:36,383
Save people. The
same as you. It's my job.

447
00:25:36,485 --> 00:25:39,987
It's who I am. It's...

448
00:25:40,089 --> 00:25:44,191
If something happened and suddenly
you couldn't be a doctor anymore,

449
00:25:44,293 --> 00:25:47,127
if someone told you you
couldn't do it anymore,

450
00:25:47,229 --> 00:25:49,091
wouldn't you wanna do
everything you could possibly do

451
00:25:49,115 --> 00:25:51,215
to be a doctor again?

452
00:25:56,321 --> 00:25:58,571
We haven't been
married 24 hours,

453
00:25:58,673 --> 00:26:00,874
and we've had our first fight.

454
00:26:00,976 --> 00:26:05,262
That's a good sign. Fighting
leads to good make-up sex.

455
00:26:07,616 --> 00:26:10,617
Are you watching birds
fly around my head again?

456
00:26:10,719 --> 00:26:13,503
Am I, like, totally
Snow White right now?

457
00:26:15,340 --> 00:26:19,009
- I just don't want to hurt him.
- He'll come around.

458
00:26:19,111 --> 00:26:22,679
It might take a while, but
once that tumor disappears,

459
00:26:22,782 --> 00:26:25,149
once you're back at work
cutting open other people,

460
00:26:25,251 --> 00:26:27,234
he'll come around.

461
00:26:30,806 --> 00:26:33,223
Is it hummingbirds at least?

462
00:26:34,760 --> 00:26:37,360
I really like hummingbirds.

463
00:26:42,267 --> 00:26:45,336
- We need to talk to Izzie.
- We are not talking Izzie

464
00:26:45,438 --> 00:26:48,472
into having surgery because
your future husband is mad at you.

465
00:26:48,574 --> 00:26:49,806
He has a right to be mad.

466
00:26:49,908 --> 00:26:51,753
We didn't talk Izzie out
of the surgery as doctors,

467
00:26:51,777 --> 00:26:56,430
- we did it as her friends.
- Our job as doctors
is to present the options,

468
00:26:56,532 --> 00:26:59,333
answer questions and let the
patient decide the course of treatment.

469
00:26:59,434 --> 00:27:03,103
- That's what we did.
- Right. Except I may have

470
00:27:03,205 --> 00:27:04,804
presented her options as,

471
00:27:04,907 --> 00:27:07,824
"You're having this
surgery over my dead body."

472
00:27:10,746 --> 00:27:13,997
He has a right to be mad.

473
00:27:14,099 --> 00:27:15,866
- Crap.
- Who is it?

474
00:27:15,968 --> 00:27:17,117
Come on.

475
00:27:18,837 --> 00:27:20,649
- Izzie, what...?
- What happened?

476
00:27:20,673 --> 00:27:23,240
- I don't know. Where's Swender!
- Izzie, let me take over.

477
00:27:23,342 --> 00:27:25,442
Yeah, Izzie, come sit down.

478
00:27:37,022 --> 00:27:39,089
The vessels and
nerves are separated.

479
00:27:39,191 --> 00:27:40,691
Skin flap is done.

480
00:27:40,793 --> 00:27:45,529
Remind me again why I'm doing
this. Someone remind me again.

481
00:27:49,068 --> 00:27:51,468
You don't know what's
gonna happen to this kid,

482
00:27:51,570 --> 00:27:56,707
how many fights he could win,
how many lives he could save.

483
00:27:58,193 --> 00:28:02,629
If you don't do this, he's
never gonna get the chance.

484
00:28:02,731 --> 00:28:06,766
We're not doing harm. We're
not hurting him. We're saving him.

485
00:28:06,868 --> 00:28:08,701
We're doing what he wants.

486
00:28:10,639 --> 00:28:12,572
It's what he wants.

487
00:28:37,816 --> 00:28:39,844
- BP's still dropping.
- We need more blood.

488
00:28:39,868 --> 00:28:42,588
- We need to move faster.
- I'm done. I'm at the end.

489
00:28:42,638 --> 00:28:44,416
I didn't see any
bowel perforation.

490
00:28:44,440 --> 00:28:46,139
It's there somewhere.
Run it again.

491
00:28:46,241 --> 00:28:48,458
- Dr...
- Run it again.

492
00:28:50,362 --> 00:28:52,212
Yes, ma'am.

493
00:28:53,498 --> 00:28:55,281
So much for IL2.

494
00:28:57,018 --> 00:28:59,536
You think this is my fault?

495
00:28:59,638 --> 00:29:03,189
- You think I did this to her?
- No, ma'am.

496
00:29:03,291 --> 00:29:06,326
There is no cure
for cancer, Dr. Yang.

497
00:29:06,428 --> 00:29:08,345
There's only us, the two of us,

498
00:29:08,447 --> 00:29:12,282
right here, fighting this thing as
aggressively as we know how.

499
00:29:12,384 --> 00:29:16,102
And sometimes that means pumping
toxins into the patient to kill the cancer.

500
00:29:16,204 --> 00:29:21,641
And, yes, sometimes, not very often,
those toxins kill the patient as well.

501
00:29:23,061 --> 00:29:26,230
Alison had three months to live
when she first came to see me,

502
00:29:26,331 --> 00:29:29,700
and I have managed to
keep her alive for two years.

503
00:29:29,802 --> 00:29:34,805
So I am not about to give up
on her, or the IL2, anytime soon,

504
00:29:34,907 --> 00:29:36,673
and neither are you.

505
00:29:45,033 --> 00:29:47,145
I wasn't asking you
to see the condo.

506
00:29:47,169 --> 00:29:50,253
I was asking you
to move in with me.

507
00:29:51,974 --> 00:29:54,724
If that's what you want.

508
00:29:56,061 --> 00:29:58,145
- I do.
- You do?

509
00:29:58,247 --> 00:30:02,315
- Yeah. Not right away.
- No, of course not. In like...

510
00:30:02,417 --> 00:30:05,001
- a year. I'm sorry, what, now?
- Ten years. Oh.

511
00:30:05,103 --> 00:30:09,422
Well, because I'll still be a
resident for six more years,

512
00:30:09,524 --> 00:30:13,327
and then I'd want to get my
practice up and running, so...

513
00:30:13,429 --> 00:30:15,395
- How about seven?
- How about five years?

514
00:30:15,497 --> 00:30:19,082
- I'll still be a resident.
- So? Stevens and Karev
are residents.

515
00:30:19,184 --> 00:30:20,394
Meredith's a resident.
Bailey's a resident.

516
00:30:20,418 --> 00:30:23,237
All married, or soon to be.

517
00:30:23,339 --> 00:30:25,872
And happily. Or whatever.

518
00:30:27,526 --> 00:30:31,795
I'm sorry, are you
asking me to marry you?

519
00:30:31,897 --> 00:30:34,847
No!

520
00:30:34,949 --> 00:30:36,650
- Why? Would you?
- Um...

521
00:30:36,752 --> 00:30:38,095
Should we be having
this conversation?

522
00:30:38,119 --> 00:30:39,836
No, probably not.

523
00:30:39,938 --> 00:30:41,454
OK...

524
00:30:41,573 --> 00:30:43,613
Impressive work
today, Dr. Bailey.

525
00:30:43,708 --> 00:30:45,608
Thank you, sir. It was fun.

526
00:30:45,710 --> 00:30:48,561
Yeah, it was, wasn't it?

527
00:30:56,171 --> 00:30:57,955
Sounds like you
guys had a good day.

528
00:30:58,057 --> 00:31:01,241
How'd the neuroblastoma kid do?

529
00:31:01,343 --> 00:31:03,393
Oh. He was awesome.
The surgery was easy,

530
00:31:03,495 --> 00:31:04,794
he gonna make a full recovery.

531
00:31:04,879 --> 00:31:06,696
That's kinda why I
wanted you there.

532
00:31:06,798 --> 00:31:08,264
Because the kids you can save

533
00:31:08,366 --> 00:31:10,516
almost make up for
the ones you can't.

534
00:31:10,618 --> 00:31:13,153
Anyways, I'm gonna go
monitor him at post-op,

535
00:31:13,255 --> 00:31:14,975
and then I'll tell his
family the good news.

536
00:31:15,056 --> 00:31:17,607
Stop by, come see the joy.

537
00:31:17,709 --> 00:31:20,110
OK.

538
00:31:28,486 --> 00:31:34,124
<i>♪ Angel wings spread
over water worn wishes ♪</i>

539
00:31:34,209 --> 00:31:39,112
<i>♪ Guarding the dreams
and the things left unsaid ♪</i>

540
00:31:39,214 --> 00:31:44,718
<i>♪ Here we are wandering,
aimlessly roaming ♪</i>

541
00:31:44,820 --> 00:31:49,823
We had to resect
part of her bowel.

542
00:31:49,925 --> 00:31:53,059
Unfortunately, we weren't
able to finish the surgery

543
00:31:53,161 --> 00:31:54,728
because she was too unstable.

544
00:31:55,964 --> 00:31:58,004
Right now, she's on a ventilator

545
00:31:58,033 --> 00:32:00,567
because she can't
breathe on her own.

546
00:32:02,588 --> 00:32:05,455
But you'll be able to
finish the surgery, right?

547
00:32:07,475 --> 00:32:10,076
Yes, if she stabilizes.

548
00:32:10,178 --> 00:32:12,562
And then she'll be able to
breathe on her own again?

549
00:32:12,664 --> 00:32:18,568
<i>♪ I don't know whether
we'll end up together ♪</i>

550
00:32:18,670 --> 00:32:20,037
<i>♪ But I always know ♪</i>

551
00:32:20,139 --> 00:32:23,440
Your daughter's heart
stopped during the surgery,

552
00:32:23,542 --> 00:32:25,892
which means her brain
wasn't getting oxygen.

553
00:32:25,994 --> 00:32:28,861
<i>♪ When it's done, we will walk
where the road meets the sun ♪</i>

554
00:32:28,963 --> 00:32:32,215
So it's unlikely she'll be
able to come off a ventilator.

555
00:32:41,359 --> 00:32:47,347
<i>- ♪ Don't disappear ♪
- ♪ Darlin', I want you ♪</i>

556
00:32:47,449 --> 00:32:52,719
<i>- ♪ Don't leave me here ♪
- ♪ And when the day comes ♪</i>

557
00:32:52,821 --> 00:32:56,222
<i>♪ I'll meet you here ♪</i>

558
00:32:57,393 --> 00:33:00,494
<i>♪ 'Cause I know that
wishes come true ♪</i>

559
00:33:01,997 --> 00:33:06,633
<i>♪ Finding my way back to you ♪</i>

560
00:33:15,043 --> 00:33:16,309
Izzie?

561
00:33:17,178 --> 00:33:21,130
Izzie. Izzie.

562
00:33:21,232 --> 00:33:23,449
- You're paging me. Are you OK?
- No.

563
00:33:23,551 --> 00:33:26,536
I don't know what to do.

564
00:33:26,638 --> 00:33:28,605
I don't know if I should
have the surgery.

565
00:33:28,707 --> 00:33:30,206
I'm gonna die either way.

566
00:33:30,308 --> 00:33:31,708
You gotta tell me what to do.

567
00:33:31,810 --> 00:33:35,645
- You know what to do.
- No, I don't.

568
00:33:37,098 --> 00:33:40,984
- I don't.
- Yes, you do.

569
00:33:41,086 --> 00:33:42,630
You're just scared to do it.

570
00:33:42,654 --> 00:33:45,338
All this back and
forth, it's just fear.

571
00:33:45,440 --> 00:33:49,709
But... you've already
made the decision.

572
00:33:51,814 --> 00:33:53,725
You made it. You made
it the second you decided

573
00:33:53,749 --> 00:33:54,926
to fight this thing.

574
00:33:54,950 --> 00:33:56,750
<i>♪ Where the road meets the sun ♪</i>

575
00:33:56,818 --> 00:33:58,084
<i>♪ And when it's done ♪</i>

576
00:33:58,186 --> 00:34:01,754
Just look... look
where you started.

577
00:34:03,141 --> 00:34:05,641
Look where you are now.

578
00:34:05,744 --> 00:34:10,646
I mean, now you're
this incredible surgeon...

579
00:34:12,050 --> 00:34:16,269
- and teacher.
- <i>♪ 'Cause I know</i>
<i>that wishes come true ♪</i>

580
00:34:16,371 --> 00:34:18,805
You're a doer, remember?

581
00:34:18,907 --> 00:34:22,275
<i>♪ Finding my way back to you ♪</i>

582
00:34:25,980 --> 00:34:29,015
You know exactly
what you have to do.

583
00:34:33,072 --> 00:34:37,423
<i>♪ Angels wings spread
over water worn wishes ♪</i>

584
00:34:37,526 --> 00:34:39,592
Come in.

585
00:34:39,694 --> 00:34:44,130
<i>♪ Guarding the dreams
and the things left unsaid ♪</i>

586
00:34:44,232 --> 00:34:45,865
<i>♪ And when it's done ♪</i>

587
00:34:45,967 --> 00:34:48,100
You can do it.

588
00:34:48,203 --> 00:34:50,170
You can cut into my brain again.

589
00:34:50,272 --> 00:34:53,189
<i>♪ When it's done, we will walk ♪</i>

590
00:34:53,292 --> 00:34:56,126
- <i>♪ Where the road</i>
<i>meets the sun ♪</i>
- OK.

591
00:34:56,228 --> 00:35:00,146
You can do it, but I don't
want to end up a vegetable.

592
00:35:00,248 --> 00:35:03,650
- Izzie, you won't...
- No, just listen.

593
00:35:03,752 --> 00:35:07,571
I want the surgery right now.
But, if something goes wrong,

594
00:35:07,673 --> 00:35:09,806
I don't want to end
up on a ventilator.

595
00:35:12,110 --> 00:35:13,910
So I'm signing a DNR.

596
00:35:14,012 --> 00:35:19,732
<i>♪ When it's done, we will walk
where the road meets the sun ♪</i>

597
00:35:25,691 --> 00:35:27,524
- Please.
- Alex...

598
00:35:27,626 --> 00:35:29,826
You went crazy. When
Denny signed that DNR,

599
00:35:29,928 --> 00:35:32,323
you went crazy. That what you
want? You want me cutting LVADs?

600
00:35:32,347 --> 00:35:34,364
You want to wreck my
career? 'Cause I will.

601
00:35:34,466 --> 00:35:39,135
I will freakin' cut LVADs
before I let you just... Wait! Stop!

602
00:35:39,237 --> 00:35:43,522
You don't get to quit.
You don't get to quit on me.

603
00:35:43,625 --> 00:35:49,028
Please. Tear it up.
The DNR. Tear it up!

604
00:35:52,000 --> 00:35:55,435
Where your eyes are
supposed to be right now,

605
00:35:55,537 --> 00:35:59,072
I see white, sandy beaches.

606
00:35:59,173 --> 00:36:00,718
And there's an ocean
behind your head

607
00:36:00,742 --> 00:36:03,977
and ghosts wandering in and out.

608
00:36:05,380 --> 00:36:07,580
I can't live like this.

609
00:36:07,682 --> 00:36:09,999
And I can't live...

610
00:36:12,504 --> 00:36:14,315
If something goes
wrong in that surgery,

611
00:36:14,339 --> 00:36:16,840
I don't want any
extraordinary measures

612
00:36:16,941 --> 00:36:21,344
taken to keep me
alive. It's not what I want.

613
00:36:21,446 --> 00:36:26,516
I went crazy when Denny signed
the DNR because I didn't understand.

614
00:36:26,618 --> 00:36:28,846
I didn't understand,
but now I do.

615
00:36:28,870 --> 00:36:33,089
And I need you to understand.

616
00:36:33,191 --> 00:36:34,869
I don't want you to go crazy.

617
00:36:34,893 --> 00:36:37,304
I want you to have
a brilliant career.

618
00:36:37,328 --> 00:36:40,430
And I hope I get to be
here for it. But if I can't,

619
00:36:40,532 --> 00:36:43,466
I just want to go
to the other side.

620
00:36:43,568 --> 00:36:46,469
I don't know what's there,
but it's gotta be better

621
00:36:46,571 --> 00:36:50,106
than hospital beds and tubes
down my throat. So please.

622
00:36:50,208 --> 00:36:53,810
Please don't cut LVADs.

623
00:36:53,912 --> 00:36:55,912
Just...

624
00:36:56,915 --> 00:37:01,184
if it comes down to it,

625
00:37:01,286 --> 00:37:03,186
just let me go.

626
00:37:12,347 --> 00:37:14,914
And right now, kiss me.

627
00:37:15,016 --> 00:37:17,583
Please just kiss me
and close your eyes,

628
00:37:17,686 --> 00:37:20,352
because the beach
is so distracting.

629
00:37:44,529 --> 00:37:46,713
I always thought it would be me.

630
00:37:48,216 --> 00:37:51,601
I'd get Alzheimer's, like my
mother, and forget everyone.

631
00:37:57,726 --> 00:37:59,792
Let's go to city hall tomorrow.

632
00:38:01,446 --> 00:38:04,914
I don't want to spend another
day not being married to you.

633
00:38:06,300 --> 00:38:08,234
OK.

634
00:38:29,724 --> 00:38:32,592
It doesn't matter
how good you are.

635
00:38:33,345 --> 00:38:35,445
Or how hard you work.

636
00:38:35,546 --> 00:38:37,380
You can do all the research,

637
00:38:37,482 --> 00:38:40,800
you can master all
the latest techniques,

638
00:38:40,902 --> 00:38:42,368
I mean, you can be the best...

639
00:38:42,471 --> 00:38:44,971
you can be the best
surgeon in the world...

640
00:38:46,507 --> 00:38:49,241
but your patients
are still gonna die.

641
00:38:52,097 --> 00:38:56,732
Because the next day or the
next month or the next year,

642
00:38:56,834 --> 00:39:00,403
you know, they're just
gonna get hit by a car

643
00:39:00,505 --> 00:39:02,472
or find a mole on their back.

644
00:39:06,127 --> 00:39:08,627
And there's nothing
you can do about it.

645
00:39:12,383 --> 00:39:14,500
I don't want you to die.

646
00:39:23,228 --> 00:39:29,265
<i>♪ For a while I had
nothing to hide ♪</i>

647
00:39:29,367 --> 00:39:30,700
You OK?

648
00:39:33,621 --> 00:39:35,972
I cut off a healthy leg.

649
00:39:36,074 --> 00:39:38,775
I just cut it off.

650
00:39:38,877 --> 00:39:40,088
It was for the
patient's own good.

651
00:39:40,112 --> 00:39:42,779
But still, I feel
like a butcher.

652
00:39:42,881 --> 00:39:48,084
My miracle case is on life
support. I thought I had one.

653
00:39:48,987 --> 00:39:52,622
One miracle.

654
00:39:52,724 --> 00:39:57,093
I hate this job sometimes.

655
00:39:57,912 --> 00:40:00,046
I don't know why we do this.

656
00:40:00,164 --> 00:40:02,382
<i>♪ Hold on to me ♪</i>

657
00:40:02,484 --> 00:40:04,683
Come on. Come with me.

658
00:40:04,785 --> 00:40:08,321
<i>♪ Hold on to me ♪</i>

659
00:40:13,228 --> 00:40:15,428
OK. What are we doing here?

660
00:40:16,464 --> 00:40:17,997
We came to see that.

661
00:40:18,099 --> 00:40:23,452
- What?
- The joy.

662
00:40:23,554 --> 00:40:25,755
It comes around rarely.

663
00:40:25,857 --> 00:40:29,225
So rarely, we
forget it can happen.

664
00:40:30,678 --> 00:40:35,031
But that... That's
why we do this.

665
00:40:35,133 --> 00:40:36,999
The joy.

666
00:40:39,287 --> 00:40:43,689
<i>♪ Some things leave
me with nothing ♪</i>

667
00:40:43,791 --> 00:40:47,277
<i>♪ I never meant to be mean ♪</i>

668
00:40:47,378 --> 00:40:49,212
<i>♪ Hold on to me ♪</i>

669
00:40:49,314 --> 00:40:52,314
<i>We spend our whole lives
worrying about the future,</i>

670
00:40:53,819 --> 00:40:57,486
<i>planning for the future,</i>

671
00:40:57,588 --> 00:41:00,656
<i>trying to predict the future.</i>

672
00:41:00,758 --> 00:41:02,625
Will you come with me?

673
00:41:08,566 --> 00:41:09,944
<i>As if figuring it out</i>

674
00:41:09,968 --> 00:41:12,268
<i>will somehow cushion the blow.</i>

675
00:41:13,471 --> 00:41:17,156
<i>But the future is
always changing.</i>

676
00:41:17,258 --> 00:41:19,125
We've got one
more. He's a doctor.

677
00:41:19,227 --> 00:41:21,877
He says he needs to do it today.

678
00:41:28,920 --> 00:41:30,236
Come in.

679
00:41:30,338 --> 00:41:32,433
<i>The future is the home
of our deepest fears...</i>

680
00:41:32,457 --> 00:41:36,309
<i>♪ Put on a straight face
to argue a lost case ♪</i>

681
00:41:36,411 --> 00:41:39,929
- <i>♪ Sometimes it's hard</i>
<i>to let go ♪</i>
- Owen?

682
00:41:40,031 --> 00:41:43,733
- Hey, Mom.
- <i>♪ Hold on to me ♪</i>

683
00:41:45,236 --> 00:41:46,102
I'm home.

684
00:41:46,204 --> 00:41:48,854
<i>♪ Hold on to me ♪</i>

685
00:41:48,956 --> 00:41:50,957
<i>and our wildest hopes.</i>

686
00:41:51,059 --> 00:41:54,210
<i>♪ Hold on to me ♪</i>

687
00:41:56,698 --> 00:41:58,731
<i>♪ Hold on to me ♪</i>

688
00:41:58,833 --> 00:42:01,834
<i>But one thing is certain:</i>

689
00:42:01,936 --> 00:42:03,336
<i>♪ Hold on to me ♪</i>

690
00:42:03,438 --> 00:42:05,938
<i>When it finally
reveals itself...</i>

691
00:42:06,040 --> 00:42:09,575
Congratulations, doctor.
Welcome to the Army.

692
00:42:09,678 --> 00:42:12,111
<i>- The future...</i>
<i>- </i> Thank you.

693
00:42:12,213 --> 00:42:14,780
<i>Is never the way we imagined it.</i>
